<main class="mc-shell mc-main">

    <!-- Learning goals -->
    <section class="mc-section">
        <div class="mc-section-header">
            <h2>Learning goals for Module 2</h2>
            <p>
                By the end of this module, students should be able to:
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="mc-card mc-card-soft">
            <ul class="mc-list">
                <li>Describe how disease transmission occurs in a massage environment.</li>
                <li>Apply standard precautions and safe hygiene practices.</li>
                <li>Identify common contraindications and precautions.</li>
                <li>Recognize anatomical endangerment sites and explain why they matter.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </section>


    <!-- Disease transmission accordion -->
    <section class="mc-section">
        <div class="mc-section-header">
            <h2>How disease transmission happens</h2>
            <p>
                Students open each section to explore the key pathways of infection in a clinical environment.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="mc-accordion" data-track-step="disease">
            <button class="mc-accordion-item">
                <span>Direct contact transmission</span>
                <span class="mc-accordion-icon">+</span>
            </button>
            <div class="mc-accordion-panel">
                <p>
                    Pathogens can pass from therapist to client or client to therapist through direct physical contact.
                    This includes contaminated hands, unwashed forearms, or touching open skin.
                </p>
            </div>

            <button class="mc-accordion-item">
                <span>Indirect contact transmission</span>
                <span class="mc-accordion-icon">+</span>
            </button>
            <div class="mc-accordion-panel">
                <p>
                    This occurs when pathogens spread through shared objects such as lotion bottles, linens,
                    headrests, door handles, or contaminated tools.
                </p>
            </div>

            <button class="mc-accordion-item">
                <span>Droplet and airborne transmission</span>
                <span class="mc-accordion-icon">+</span>
            </button>
            <div class="mc-accordion-panel">
                <p>
                    Talking, coughing, or sneezing can transmit pathogens through the air. Proper ventilation,
                    therapist health screening, and rescheduling sick clients protect the treatment room.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>


    <!-- Tools and hygiene flip cards -->
    <section class="mc-section">
        <div class="mc-section-header">
            <h2>Hygiene essentials</h2>
            <p>
                Students tap each card to learn the most important hygiene habits for massage therapists.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="mc-grid mc-grid-2 mc-flip-grid" data-track-step="hygiene">
            <button class="mc-flipcard" type="button">
                <div class="mc-flip-inner">
                    <div class="mc-flip-front">
                        <p class="mc-label">Hand washing</p>
                        <p class="mc-flip-front-text">Tap to review proper hand hygiene.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="mc-flip-back">
                        <ul class="mc-list">
                            <li>Wash hands before and after every client.</li>
                            <li>Use warm water and soap for at least 20 seconds.</li>
                            <li>Dry completely using a clean towel or paper towels.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </button>

            <button class="mc-flipcard" type="button">
                <div class="mc-flip-inner">
                    <div class="mc-flip-front">
                        <p class="mc-label">Surface sanitation</p>
                        <p class="mc-flip-front-text">Tap to review surface cleaning steps.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="mc-flip-back">
                        <ul class="mc-list">
                            <li>Disinfect all surfaces between clients.</li>
                            <li>Pay extra attention to face cradle, table, and bolsters.</li>
                            <li>Use approved disinfectants with correct contact time.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </button>

            <button class="mc-flipcard" type="button">
                <div class="mc-flip-inner">
                    <div class="mc-flip-front">
                        <p class="mc-label">Linens</p>
                        <p class="mc-flip-front-text">Tap for linen handling rules.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="mc-flip-back">
                        <ul class="mc-list">
                            <li>Use fresh linens for every client.</li>
                            <li>Place used linens in a closed bin.</li>
                            <li>Wash in hot water with appropriate detergents.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </button>

            <button class="mc-flipcard" type="button">
                <div class="mc-flip-inner">
                    <div class="mc-flip-front">
                        <p class="mc-label">Therapist health</p>
                        <p class="mc-flip-front-text">Tap for therapist illness policy.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="mc-flip-back">
                        <ul class="mc-list">
                            <li>Do not work while ill.</li>
                            <li>Reschedule clients if you show signs of infection.</li>
                            <li>Wear a mask if recovering from respiratory symptoms.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </button>

        </div>
    </section>



    <!-- Hotspot activity: Endangerment sites -->
    <section class="mc-section">
        <div class="mc-section-header">
            <h2>Endangerment sites</h2>
            <p>
                Students tap labeled areas to learn what to avoid and why these sites matter in bodywork.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="mc-card mc-card-soft" data-track-step="endangerment">
            <p class="mc-question">Tap each site to review what to avoid and how to work safely around it.</p>

            <div class="mc-endangerment-map">
                <button class="mc-endangerment-spot" data-info="Avoid deep pressure over the carotid artery. Use gentle strokes on the neck.">Neck</button>
                <button class="mc-endangerment-spot" data-info="Avoid direct pressure to the axilla. Lymph nodes and neurovascular bundles lie here.">Axilla</button>
                <button class="mc-endangerment-spot" data-info="Avoid pressure to the medial upper arm along the brachial artery.">Upper arm</button>
                <button class="mc-endangerment-spot" data-info="Avoid deep pressure behind the knee. Popliteal artery and nerve bundle are here.">Knee</button>
                <button class="mc-endangerment-spot" data-info="Avoid strong pressure on the abdomen unless trained and client consents.">Abdomen</button>
            </div>

            <div id="endangermentInfo" class="mc-endangerment-info"></div>
        </div>
    </section>


    <!-- Quiz -->
    <section class="mc-section">
        <div class="mc-section-header">
            <h2>Contraindication quiz</h2>
            <p>
                Students read each situation and decide if massage is safe, requires adaptation, or should be postponed.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="mc-card mc-card-soft" data-track-step="contra-quiz">

            <p class="mc-question">
                A client arrives with a fever of 101 but wants a light massage to relax. What do you do?
            </p>

            <form id="contraQuizForm" class="mc-quiz">
                <label class="mc-quiz-option">
                    <input type="radio" name="contraChoice" value="A">
                    <span>Give the massage lightly to help reduce stress.</span>
                </label>

                <label class="mc-quiz-option">
                    <input type="radio" name="contraChoice" value="B">
                    <span>Postpone the appointment. Fever indicates a systemic infection.</span>
                </label>

                <label class="mc-quiz-option">
                    <input type="radio" name="contraChoice" value="C">
                    <span>Massage only the feet to avoid circulating pathogens.</span>
                </label>

                <button type="submit" class="mc-button mc-button-primary">
                    Check my answer
                </button>
            </form>

            <div id="contraQuizFeedback" class="mc-quiz-feedback" aria-live="polite"></div>
        </div>
    </section>



    <!-- Reflection -->
    <section class="mc-section">
        <div class="mc-section-header">
            <h2>Reflection prompt</h2>
            <p>
                This helps students connect hygiene and safety practices to real-life client situations.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="mc-card mc-card-soft" data-track-step="reflection">
            <p class="mc-reflection-question">
                Think about any moment when you have felt unwell or low energy but pushed through anyway.
                How can understanding infection control help you make better choices for yourself and clients?
            </p>

            <textarea id="reflectionInput" class="mc-textarea" rows="4"
                placeholder="Students can type their thoughts here. This saves in their browser only."></textarea>

            <div class="mc-reflection-actions">
                <button type="button" class="mc-button mc-button-secondary" id="saveReflectionButton">
                    Save reflection to this device
                </button>
                <span id="reflectionStatus" class="mc-reflection-status"></span>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>



